article.headline: UTEP 92, Toledo 91
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Stefon Jackson scored 20 points to help Texas-El Paso to a 92-71 win over Toledo on Saturday in the consolation game of the Sun Bowl Tournament. Kevin Henderson finished with 16 points, nine rebounds and five assists for the Miners (7-6). Also scoring in double figures were Marvin Kilgore with 16 points, Darren Clarke with 12 and Maurice Thomas with 11. Henderson and Clarke both contributed to the 34 points scored by the UTEP bench, compared to 18 points from the Rockets' bench. Malik Alvin's three steals led the Miners, who forced Toledo (4-7) into 27 turnovers. UTEP scored 39 points off turnovers, to the Rockets' 15. Justin Ingram scored a game-high 24 points for Toledo. Keonta Howell scored 13 and Florentino Valencia added 12. Ridley Johnson finished with nine points and nine rebounds.
